A page is a fixed-size block of data that your database reads/writes at once from disk.
Why 4096 bytes?
    OS disk block = 4KB
    CPU cache friendly
    Used by SQLite, PostgreSQL, MySQL

endianess


A file is simply:
    A long line of bytes stored on disk

Byte index: 0   1   2   3   4   5
File data:  H   E   L   L   O


